==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|ni}}

===Adverb===
'''niin'''

# [[so]], [[then]], in that case.
# An affirmative answer to a question or comment: [[yes]], [[yeah]].
#:''Eilenkö sinä maksoit laskun?'' ''Niin.''
#:"Did you pay the bill yesterday?" "Yes."

====Usage notes====
*''Niin'' as an answer often has an additional meaning of "of course". As in the example, the interrogative suffix ''[[-ko|-ko/kö]]'' is usually attached to the point of the question.

===Conjunction===
'''niin'''

#[[so]], [[in order that]].
#Used to introduce the main clause after ''if'' clause: [[then]].
#:''Jos yöllä on selkeää, niin tulee kova pakkanen.''
#:"If it's clear at night then it'll be heavy frost."

====Usage notes====
*When used in conjunction with ''[[jos]]'' "if", ''niin'' can often be omitted when no emphasis is desired.

